post_text: September 8th is World or International Literacy Day. Since 1966, the United Nations has celebrated the importance of literacy on this day. This year, the focus is on ‚ÄúLiteracy teaching and learning in the COVID-19 crisis and beyond,‚Äù especially recognizing the role of educators play in literacy. Visit https://www.un.org/en/observances/literacy-day for more information. Also, take some time today to thank those who helped you learn how to read. Read. Learn. Grow. #WorldLiteracyDay2020

post_text:
The ABCFT Retiree Chapter presented Allyson Grace Francisco, 2020 CHS graduate and former Carver student, with its annual $2500 scholarship. Allyson Francisco will be attending Cal State Fullerton.

The scholarship is given each year to a graduating ABCUSD senior who is planning to become a teacher. The scholarship is given in the name of an ABC Teacher. This year it was given in the commemoration of Ethel Bowman, a teacher in ABC from 1967 to 2003. She last worked at Nixon Elementary School. The scholarship encourages students to pursue teaching in public education. This is ABCFT Retiree Chapter's 8th Scholarship. Past winners have been from AHS, CHS, GHS, and WHS.

Google Meet

Workshops will be offered both in the morning and evening.

ABCUSD

post_text: The 2020-2021 meal service is up and running! Meals are served from 2:00 p.m. to 3:30 p.m. Monday through Friday at all ABCUSD elementary school sites. Unlike this past spring, the District is not able to serve free meals to all families. Meals will be charged based on student eligibility ‚Äì free, reduced price, or free. Meal ID Cards have been sent to families in the meal service program and must be presented to pick up a meal. Additional pick up times are available at some sites. Visit the nutrition services website for more information: https://abcafe.us/

COVID-19 Testing Information

Los Angeles County residents who are in need of being tested for COVID-19 have many options. First, contact your primary health care provider or healthcare center about receiving a test at their facility. If you do not have access to care or are unable to contact them, there are free testing sites located across Los Angeles County. Please use the following link for more information: https://covid19.lacounty.gov/testing/

Please stay healthy and safe.

Sincerely,

ABC Unified School District

Thank you very much, and please stay healthy and safe.

Sincerely,

Dr. Mary Sieu
Superintendent

Rep. Linda S√°nchez
June 2 at 12:48 PM ¬∑

Thank you again to everyone who participated in this year's Congressional Art Competition. I received more than 160 entries from 15 high schools throughout the district. Here are the overall winners.

1st Place: Berry-Spotted Skeleton Tarantula by Ruby Mai-Ly Kirk, La Serna High School

2nd place: Everything by Isabella Robles, La Serna High School

3rd place: Drying, Drying, Dried by Karina Rivera, El Rancho High School

Honorable Mention: Tears of Prayer by Arrium Jung, Whitney High School

Fan Favorite: Pull by Anne Guzman, Mayfair High School

post_text:
Dear ABC Families,

The Online Learning at Home program begins today, March 19. Please visit our website at olah.abcusd.us for more information regarding your student's first day of online learning at home, technical support, and more.

Please allow for today and tomorrow to be a time of transition. The District will engage with you to problem-solve, provide continued access to the Internet and devices for families in need, and to ensure engagement with our online classrooms.

Please contact ABC's Online Learning at Home Technical Support Center at (562) 229-7929 should you have related questions.

post_text:
During the next two weeks, Nutrition Services will be serving "grab-and-go" meals at our schools, students will grab a meal and enjoy it at home and not on campus. The schedule is as follows:

Monday - March 16, 2020, 8:00 - 8:30 Breakfast will be available at schools that serve breakfast
Monday - March 16, 2020, 11:30 to 12:00 Students will pick up lunch for that day and breakfast for the next day.
This process will be repeated for the rest of the week.

This means, Monday, March 16, 2020, will be the only day that students will need to pick up breakfast.

Schools will be closed for the next two Fridays, so on Thursday, the students will pick up lunch for Thursday, breakfast for Friday, lunch for Friday, and breakfast for the following Monday.

Thank you for your patience as we move through these next two weeks.
text:
During the next two weeks, Nutrition Services will be serving "grab-and-go" meals at our schools, students will grab a meal and enjoy it at home and not on campus. The schedule is as follows:

Monday - March 16, 2020, 8:00 - 8:30 Breakfast will be available at schools that serve breakfast
Monday - March 16, 2020, 11:30 to 12:00 Students will pick up lunch for that day and breakfast for the next day.
This process will be repeated for the rest of the week.

This means, Monday, March 16, 2020, will be the only day that students will need to pick up breakfast.

Schools will be closed for the next two Fridays, so on Thursday, the students will pick up lunch for Thursday, breakfast for Friday, lunch for Friday, and breakfast for the following Monday.

Thank you for your patience as we move through these next two weeks.
